subtests.name: Relative URL-like specifier keys / should absolutize strings prefixed with ./, ../, or / into the corresponding URLs
Relative URL-like specifier keys / should not absolutize strings prefixed with ./, ../, or / with a data: URL base
Relative URL-like specifier keys / should absolutize the literal strings ./, ../, or / with no suffix
Relative URL-like specifier keys / should treat percent-encoded variants of ./, ../, or / as bare specifiers
Absolute URL specifier keys / should only accept absolute URL specifier keys with fetch schemes, treating others as bare specifiers
Absolute URL specifier keys / should parse absolute URLs, treating unparseable ones as bare specifiers
Absolute URL specifier keys / should parse built-in module specifier keys, including with a "/"
